  • Type Parameters:
    RequiredElementType - means the required type from the list of allowed types below that implement WebElement Instances of the defined type will be returned via findElement* and findElements*. Warning (!!!). Allowed types:
    WebElement

      • hideKeyboard

        public void hideKeyboard(String strategy,
                String keyName)
        Description copied from interface: IOSDeviceActionShortcuts
        Hides the keyboard if it is showing. Available strategies are PRESS_KEY and TAP_OUTSIDE. One taps outside the keyboard, the other presses a key of your choosing (probably the 'Done' key). Hiding the keyboard often depends on the way an app is implemented, no single strategy always works.
        Specified by:
        hideKeyboard in interface IOSDeviceActionShortcuts
        Parameters:
        strategy - HideKeyboardStrategy
        keyName - a String, representing the text displayed on the button of the keyboard you want to press. For example: "Done"
        See Also:
        IOSDeviceActionShortcuts.hideKeyboard(String, String)
